{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-13839/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-13839"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:38:39"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["plan américain"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["group shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man and woman talk to another man."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13839/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-13839","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13839/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-13839"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13839/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13839/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13839/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13839/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13839/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13839/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13839/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13839/canvas/1/1fa50144-3abe-4ef7-b3ed-0ccf7622bde1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T14:29:56.400Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds bristles at Dr. Hardy’s claim that he’s been “laid siege by much worse.” In his mind, there’s none more powerful than he. He also recalls “barking” at Dr. Hardy, a choice of words that is significant for two reasons. First, Reynolds owns several <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW134267593 BCX2\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-01942.html\"><u>dogs</u></a> who appear briefly in one scene and then disappear from the film. Second, despite his highly choreographed routines and outwardly composed appearance, there’s something ferocious within him that occasionally comes out in moments of frustration. Along with Reynolds, <em>There Will Be Blood</em>’s<em> </em>Daniel Plainview and <em>The Master</em>’s Lancaster Dodd are similar men of power who throw temper tantrums when provoked.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-13839/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1056.6233766233765,162.07792207792204,367.79220779220805,842.3376623376627"}}}]}]}]}